Niger State Police Command has arrested a 32-year-old man, Sani Garba for raping a 60-year-old woman in Kuspa in Suleja local government area of the state. The police public relations officer in charge of the command, Wasiu Abiodun, said that based on information received, police operatives attached to ‘B’ Division, Suleja, arrested the suspect in  Kuspa area of the town. He said that the suspect  had  “criminally trespassed into the room of the 60-year-old woman of same address and had canal knowledge of her.” According to him, the suspect has confessed to entering the woman’s room and forced her into the act and that the suspect would  soon be arraigned in court. Similarly, he said acting on a tip off, police operatives attached to ‘B’ Division, Kontangora arrested one John Adamu aged 23 years of Ungwan Nassarawa area of Kontangora, for sexually assaulting a seven-year-old girl of the same address. He said that the suspect confessed to have penetrated the girl through the back at his security post premises and the suspect would also be arraigned in court soon. Meanwhile, six suspects have been nabbed in possession of canabis.   Based on a tip-off, police detectives attached to Maitumbi Division arrested one Usman Adamu 28 years, Abdullahi Usman 32 years,  Martins Okwor 30 years, Abdullahi Ibrahim 33 years, Ashiru Garba 25 years and Kabiru Ibrahim 28 years.